<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

      <h1>Tech support</h1>
      <p>
        Launchpad&#8217;s tech support system
        lets people request help with applications or distributions,
        and lets anyone help resolve those requests.
      </p>
      <h2>Latest support requests</h2>
      <table>
        <tal:ticket
          repeat="ticket context/latest_tickets"
          content="structure ticket/@@+listing-detailed"
        />
      </table>
      <p>
        These requests are from across the whole of Launchpad.
        To see the requests for a <a href="/products">product</a> or
        <a href="/distros/">distribution</a>,
        visit the page for that product or distribution.
      </p>
    </div>

<metal:help fill-slot="help">
  <p>This page gives you a quick overview of the recent
  activity in the Launchpad support tracker.
  </p>
  <p>To post a new support request, navigate to the product or distribution
    you are having a problem with and use the <emph>Request Support</emph>
    menu item.
  </p>
  <p><a href="https://help.launchpad.net/SupportTrackerDocumentation">Extensive
      documention</a> for the support tracker application is available in the
    Help wiki.</p>
</metal:help>
  </body>
</html>
